First, we note that 6 and 10 can form even numbers starting from 6, but not all even numbers. Adding 15 (an odd number) allows forming odd numbers. We can form even numbers starting from 16 (6 + 10) and odd numbers starting from 15 (itself). Checking specific numbers: - 17, 19, 23, and 29 cannot be formed with 6, 10, and 15. - 29 is the largest number that cannot be formed by any combination of these coins. However, upon further verification: - 38 can be formed as \(10 \times 2 + 6 \times 3 = 20 + 18 = 38\). - Numbers starting from 31 can be formed using combinations of 6, 10, and 15. Thus, the largest number that cannot be formed is 29. The sum of the digits of 29 is \(2 + 9 = 11\). \[ \boxed{11} \]
